cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with brain MRI scans and proposes a Siamese neural network for learning a representation that minimizes between-scanner variation while maintaining contrast between brain tissues. This involves image processing, machine learning, and neural networks, which are all covered by the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for representation learning (cs.AI), and the evaluation of the proposed method on both simulated and real MRI data (cs.NE, cs.MM).
